      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "step2",
          "action": "Heat sunflower oil in a small saucepan over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the finely sliced garlic, sliced chillies, and star anise. Fry for 2–2½ minutes, stirring to separate the garlic slices, until the garlic is crisp and pale golden. Strain through a sieve set over a small heatproof bowl to collect the oil. Set the fried chilli and garlic aside, and reserve 80ml of the aromatic oil for another recipe. Combine the remaining 40ml of oil with the toasted sesame seeds, maple syrup, rice vinegar, and soy sauce to make the dressing.",
