          "action": "Preheat the oven to 200°C fan. Place the roasted celeriac wedges on a parchment-lined baking tray, cut side up, brushed with their cooking oil and celeriac caramel (or with some olive oil and a little maple syrup or honey if not already done). Roast for 20 minutes, or until golden-brown.",
